## Test Case
Verify soft-deleted patients are excluded from GET /patients list responses.

## File
tests/Feature/Patient/PatientApiTest.php

## Test Design
```php
it('excludes soft-deleted patients from list', function () {
    $admin = User::factory()->admin()->create();
    $active = Patient::factory()->create(['first_name' => 'Active']);
    $deleted = Patient::factory()->create(['first_name' => 'Deleted']);
    $deleted->delete();

    $response = $this->actingAs($admin)
        ->getJson('/api/patients');

    $response->assertOk();

    $ids = collect($response->json('data'))->pluck('id')->map(fn($id) => (int) $id)->all();
    expect($ids)->toContain($active->id)
        ->not->toContain($deleted->id);
});
```

## Acceptance
- [ ] Creates one active and one soft-deleted patient
- [ ] Asserts 200 OK
- [ ] Asserts active patient id is in response data
- [ ] Asserts deleted patient id is NOT in response data

## Test Case
Verify admin can DELETE a patient and both the patient and their socioeconomic record are soft-deleted.

## File
tests/Feature/Patient/PatientApiTest.php

## Test Design
```php
it('allows admin to soft-delete patient and cascades to socioeconomic', function () {
    $admin = User::factory()->admin()->create();
    $patient = Patient::factory()->hasSocioeconomic()->create();
    $socioId = $patient->socioeconomic->id;

    $response = $this->actingAs($admin)
        ->deleteJson("/api/patients/{$patient->id}");

    $response->assertNoContent();

    $this->assertSoftDeleted('patients', ['id' => $patient->id]);
    $this->assertSoftDeleted('patient_socioeconomic', ['id' => $socioId]);
});
```

## Acceptance
- [ ] Creates patient with socioeconomic
- [ ] Sends DELETE request as admin
- [ ] Asserts 204 No Content
- [ ] Asserts patient has deleted_at set (assertSoftDeleted)
- [ ] Asserts patient_socioeconomic has deleted_at set

## Test Case
Verify admin can PATCH patient fields and changes are persisted.

## File
tests/Feature/Patient/PatientApiTest.php

## Test Design
```php
it('allows admin to update patient fields', function () {
    $admin = User::factory()->admin()->create();
    $patient = Patient::factory()->create(['first_name' => 'Old']);

    $response = $this->actingAs($admin)
        ->patchJson("/api/patients/{$patient->id}", [
            'firstName' => 'Updated',
            'phone' => '+387 61 999 888',
        ]);

    $response->assertOk()
        ->assertJsonPath('data.attributes.firstName', 'Updated');

    $this->assertDatabaseHas('patients', [
        'id' => $patient->id,
        'first_name' => 'Updated',
        'phone' => '+387 61 999 888',
    ]);
});
```

## Acceptance
- [ ] Creates patient with known first_name
- [ ] PATCHes firstName and phone
- [ ] Asserts 200 OK
- [ ] Asserts updated firstName in JSON:API response
- [ ] Asserts updated row in database

