## Task
Verify and update app/Policies/PatientPolicy.php to enforce correct role-based access

## Required Authorization Matrix
| Method | Admin | Doctor | Patient (own) | Patient (other) |
|--------|-------|--------|---------------|-----------------|
| viewAny | YES | YES | YES (filtered in controller) | N/A |
| view | YES | YES | YES | NO (403) |
| create | YES | YES | NO | NO |
| update | YES | YES | YES | NO (403) |
| delete | YES | YES | NO | NO |
| forceDelete | YES | NO | NO | NO |

## Current Implementation (verify and update viewAny)
The existing viewAny may only return true for admin/doctor. It MUST be updated to also return true for patients — the controller index() will apply the user_id filter. If viewAny returns false for patients, the controller authorize() call will 403 all patient list requests.

```php
public function viewAny(User $user): bool
{
    // Allow all authenticated roles — controller filters results by role
    return $user->isAdmin() || $user->isDoctor() || $user->isPatient();
}

public function view(User $user, Patient $patient): bool
{
    return $user->isAdmin() || $user->isDoctor() || $user->id === $patient->user_id;
}

public function create(User $user): bool
{
    return $user->isAdmin() || $user->isDoctor();
}

public function update(User $user, Patient $patient): bool
{
    return $user->isAdmin() || $user->isDoctor() || $user->id === $patient->user_id;
}

public function delete(User $user, Patient $patient): bool
{
    return $user->isAdmin() || $user->isDoctor();
}

public function forceDelete(User $user, Patient $patient): bool
{
    return $user->isAdmin();
}
```

## Acceptance
- [ ] viewAny returns true for admin, doctor, AND patient
- [ ] view allows own record for patient, all records for admin/doctor
- [ ] create allows admin/doctor only (NOT patient)
- [ ] update allows own record for patient, all for admin/doctor
- [ ] delete allows admin/doctor only (NOT patient)
- [ ] forceDelete allows admin only

