## Task
Create app/Http/Resources/Api/PatientResource.php with JSON:API v1 compliance

## Design
```php
namespace App\Http\Resources\Api;

use Illuminate\Http\Request;
use Illuminate\Http\Resources\Json\JsonResource;

class PatientResource extends JsonResource
{
    public function toArray(Request $request): array
    {
        return [
            'type' => 'patient',
            'id' => (string) $this->id,
            'attributes' => [
                'firstName' => $this->first_name,
                'lastName' => $this->last_name,
                'fullName' => $this->full_name,
                'dateOfBirth' => $this->date_of_birth?->toDateString(),
                'gender' => $this->gender,
                'phone' => $this->phone,
                'address' => $this->address,
                'city' => $this->city,
                'postalCode' => $this->postal_code,
                'emergencyContactName' => $this->emergency_contact_name,
                'emergencyContactPhone' => $this->emergency_contact_phone,
                'bloodType' => $this->blood_type,
                'allergies' => $this->allergies,
                'medicalNotes' => $this->medical_notes,
                'createdAt' => $this->created_at?->toIso8601String(),
                'updatedAt' => $this->updated_at?->toIso8601String(),
            ],
            'relationships' => [
                'user' => [
                    'data' => $this->whenLoaded('user', fn() => [
                        'type' => 'user',
                        'id' => (string) $this->user->id,
                    ]),
                ],
                'socioeconomic' => [
                    'data' => $this->whenLoaded('socioeconomic', fn() => $this->socioeconomic ? [
                        'type' => 'patient_socioeconomic',
                        'id' => (string) $this->socioeconomic->id,
                    ] : null),
                ],
            ],
        ];
    }

    public function with(Request $request): array
    {
        $included = [];
        if ($this->relationLoaded('socioeconomic') && $this->socioeconomic) {
            $included[] = new PatientSocioeconomicResource($this->socioeconomic);
        }
        return $included ? ['included' => $included] : [];
    }
}
```

## Acceptance
- [ ] JSON:API structure: type, id, attributes, relationships
- [ ] All attribute keys are camelCase
- [ ] Relationships include user and socioeconomic
- [ ] included array populated when relationships loaded

## Task
Create app/Services/PatientService.php for transactional CRUD operations

## Design
```php
namespace App\Services;

use App\Models\Patient;
use App\Models\PatientSocioeconomic;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\DB;

class PatientService
{
    public function createPatient(array $patientData, ?array $socioeconomicData = null): Patient
    {
        return DB::transaction(function () use ($patientData, $socioeconomicData) {
            $patient = Patient::create($patientData);
            if ($socioeconomicData) {
                $patient->socioeconomic()->create($socioeconomicData);
            }
            return $patient->load('socioeconomic', 'user');
        });
    }

    public function updatePatient(Patient $patient, array $patientData, ?array $socioeconomicData = null): Patient
    {
        return DB::transaction(function () use ($patient, $patientData, $socioeconomicData) {
            $patient->update($patientData);
            if ($socioeconomicData !== null) {
                $patient->socioeconomic()->updateOrCreate(
                    ['patient_id' => $patient->id],
                    $socioeconomicData
                );
            }
            return $patient->fresh(['socioeconomic', 'user']);
        });
    }
}
```

## Acceptance
- [ ] PatientService class created
- [ ] createPatient() uses DB::transaction
- [ ] createPatient() creates patient and optional socioeconomic atomically
- [ ] updatePatient() uses DB::transaction
- [ ] updatePatient() updates patient and creates/updates socioeconomic

Build the single source of truth for all API response shapes. ALL controllers must use this trait — direct response()->json() calls are forbidden after this task is done.

ENVELOPE FORMAT (LARAVEL_API_RULES.md §2): success responses use {message, status, data}; validation errors use {message, errors}. The HTTP status code goes in BOTH the response header AND the body status field — the body field helps clients that parse JSON without inspecting headers.

COMMAND: php artisan make:class Traits/ApiResponses --no-interaction, then convert the generated class to a trait.

METHODS TO IMPLEMENT:
- ok(string $message, mixed $data = null): JsonResponse — HTTP 200, body {message, status: 200, data}
- created(string $message, mixed $data = null): JsonResponse — HTTP 201, body {message, status: 201, data}
- noContent(): JsonResponse — HTTP 204, empty body
- error(string $message, int $status = 400, mixed $data = null): JsonResponse — HTTP $status, body {message, status, data}

TDD CYCLE: (1) write tests/Feature/Api/ApiResponsesTest.php — test each method envelope shape via GET /api/ping, run to confirm RED; (2) implement the trait methods per the spec above; (3) run tests to confirm GREEN; (4) vendor/bin/pint --dirty + composer run analyse.

WHY CENTRALISE: if the envelope format ever changes, one file changes — not every controller.
